A square and a right triangle have equal perimeters. The legs of the right triangle are 20 inches and 15 inches. The task is to find the area of the square, in square inches.The right triangle can be represented as: egin{tikzpicture}\draw (0,0) -- (3,0) -- (3,4) -- cycle;\draw (1.5,0) -- (1.5,0.2) -- (1.7,0.2) -- (1.7,0);
ode at (1.5,-0.3) {15};
ode at (3.3,2) {20};
ode at (1.2,2) {$x$};\end{tikzpicture}

Bobby, Sam, and Eric are standing in a line. The distance between Bobby and Sam is 10 feet, and the distance between Bobby and Eric is 8 feet. The problem is to find the minimum possible distance between Eric and Sam. egin{tikzpicture}\draw (0,0) -- (10,0);\draw (0,0) -- (8,0);
ode at (0,0) [above left] {Bobby};
ode at (10,0) [above right] {Sam};
ode at (8,0) [above] {Eric};\end{tikzpicture}
